---
description: Module architecture rules
alwaysApply: true
---

# Module Architecture Rules

Follow:

docs/01-architecture.md (canonical)

docs/08-module-architecture.md

---

# Module Location

All modules must live in:

src/modules

---

# Business Module Flow

Page

↓

Hook

↓

Use Case

↓

Repository

↓

Database

---

# Business Module Structure

Every business module must follow:

module/

├── components/
├── pages/
├── hooks/
├── use-cases/
├── repositories/
├── schemas/
├── types/
└── index.ts

Do not create services/ inside business modules.

---

# Repository Rule

Database access only inside:

repositories/

Never access database directly from:

- pages
- components
- hooks

---

# Use Case Rule

Business logic belongs in:

use-cases/

Do not place business logic in:

- pages
- components
- hooks
- repositories

---

# Auth Module Exception

auth/ is a platform module — not a business module.

Auth module may use:

api/
hooks/
components/
pages/
schemas/
types/

Auth module does NOT require:

- use-cases/
- repositories/

AuthProvider implementations belong in:

backend/Template.Infrastructure/Auth/

Auth orchestration belongs in:

backend/Template.API/CoreFeatures/Auth/
backend/Template.Core/Features/Auth/
backend/Template.Infrastructure/Auth/
frontend/src/features/auth/

Auth module must not depend directly on Supabase or any specific provider.

---

# Schema Rule

Validation schemas belong in:

schemas/

Use:

Zod

---

# Type Rule

Shared module types belong in:

types/

---

# Hook Rule

React hooks belong in:

hooks/

Examples:

use-users

use-create-user

---

# Public API Rule

Every module must expose:

index.ts

Consumers must import from:

modules/module-name

Not from internal paths.

---

# Shared Code

Shared reusable code belongs in:

frontend/src/shared/

Examples:

components

hooks

utils

constants

types

config

---

# Module Isolation

Modules should be loosely coupled.

Avoid direct access to another module's internal files.

---

# Tenant Model

Current architecture:

One Customer = One Database

Do not add organization_id to new tables unless explicitly requested for future multi-tenant work.

---

# Goal

Modules must be:

- Independent
- Reusable
- Scalable
- Maintainable
- AI Friendly
